	<entry name="SteelLegionAutocannon" value="Voss Pattern Autocannon"/>
	<entry name="SteelLegionAutocannonFlavor" value="Typically mounted on vehicles, autocannons are large autoguns capable of firing a variety of large munitions. While a sole Space Marine can wield one, it teams a team of Guardsmen to operate even a mounted autocannon. The forces of Armageddon, in their constant battles with the Orks, need weapons capable of taking on massive hordes, tanks, and skimming helicopters. The Adeptus Mechanicus on the Forge World of Voss posseses an STC hidden from their peers, which allows them to produce compact autocannons from scavenged, damaged autocannons."/>
	<entry name="SteelLegionHeavyBolter" value="Voss Pattern Heavy Bolter"/>
	<entry name="SteelLegionHeavyBolterFlavor" value="While most Heavy Bolters are mounted in vehicle chassis, Guardsmen commonly have Heavy Weapons Squads wield them mounted on tripods, especially when dug in behind cover. The Tech-priests of Voss produced a lighter variant, more suited for the mechanised forces of the Steel Legion. &quot;Lighter&quot; doesn't mean &quot;not heavy,&quot; especially not in terms of firepower. Just as they still need setup, Voss Pattern Heavy Bolters are still capable of spitting a stream of death upon the foe."/>
	<entry name="SteelLegionHeavyBolterSuppressing" value="Lay Down Suppressing Fire"/>
	<entry name="SteelLegionHeavyBolterSuppressingDescription" value="Fires Pinning shots at greater range, with greatly reduced damage."/>
